The paper presents a data structure for answering proximity queries in geometric data, which suggests it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Additionally, the paper discusses density estimation, which could place it in cs.DB (Databases) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper also discusses sampling and estimation, which could place it in cs.IT (Information Theory).
